tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured laboratory values are within normal limits. Glycemic control (HbA1c, glucose) is adequate, and renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are normal. No laboratory evidence of acute or chronic metabolic, renal, or electrolyte disturbances at this time. Recommend continued routine monitoring.
